Re8 14. c4 e5 15. dxe5 Nxe5 16. cxd5 Nxf3+ 17. Bxf3 Nc3 18. Rxc3 Bxc3 {Kamsky,
G (2721)-Mamedyarov,S (2757) Beijing 2013 0-1 (67)}) (4. Nd2 d6 5. h3 O-O 6.
Bh2 c5 7. c3 Nc6 8. Ngf3 cxd4 9. exd4 e5 10. dxe5 dxe5 11. Nc4 Nd5 12. Be2 e4
13. Nfd2 e3 14. Nxe3 Nxe3 15. fxe3 Qh4+ 16. Kf1 Qe7 17. Nf3 Qxe3 18. Qd3 Bh6 {
Pirs,M (2330)-Heiling,T (2215) Hessen 2000 0-1 (43)}) 4... d5 5. Be2 h5 (5...
c5 6. Nc3 $11) 6. Nc3 c6 {Prevents intrusion on b5} 7. Nf3 Bf5 8. Ne5 Nbd7 9.
f3 {Controls e4} Bh6 10. Bxh6 Rxh6 11. Qd2 Rh7 12. O-O-O Nxe5 (12... Qc7 13.
Nxd7 Qxd7 14. b3 $11) 13. dxe5 $14 Nd7 14. e4 dxe4 15. fxe4 (15. g4 $142 hxg4
16. fxg4 $14) 15... Bg4 $4 {a transit from better to worse} (15... Be6 $142 $11
{and Black can hope to survive}) 16. Bxg4 $18 hxg4 17. e6 $1 {surprise!} Nc5 $4
{Black has lost his nerve... understandable when you consider his position} (
17... fxe6 18. Qg5 {Combination}) 18. exf7+ Rxf7 19. Qg5 Qc7 20. Qxc5 Rd8 21.
Rxd8+ Kxd8 22. Rd1+ Ke8 23. e5 b6 (23... Rf5 {doesn't change anything anymore}
24. Qxa7 Kf7 25. Kb1 $18) 24. Qd4 (24. Nb5 $142 {makes it even easier for White
} Qc8 25. Qc4 $18) 24... c5 (24... Rf5 {is the last straw} 25. Qxg4 Kf7 26. e6+
Kg7 $18) 25. Qd5 (25. Qxg4 $142 {nails it down} Qc6 26. e6 Rf6 $18) 25... Qc8
26. Ne4 (26. Ne4 Kf8 27. h5 $18) 1-0

