Ginzburg,M (2406)-Bademian Orchanian,J (2165) Punta del Este 1999 1-0 (41)}) 7.
Be3 {Black is behind in developement} Bg7 {[%cal Rc6d4,Rd8d4,Rg7d4,Gd1d4,Ge3d4,
Gf3d4] Pawn d4, live or die!} 8. c3 {Consolidates b4} (8. Nc3 O-O $11) 8... O-O
9. O-O Bf5 10. Nbd2 e5 (10... Qd7 11. Nc4 $11) 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 13.
Re1 Re8 14. Qc1 Nd5 15. Nf3 Bf6 $4 (15... Nxe3 16. Rxe3 Bf6 17. Rxe8+ Qxe8 18.
Qf4 $11) 16. Bd4 (16. Rd1 $142 {and White takes home the point} c6 17. c4 $18)
16... Rxe1+ $14 17. Qxe1 Bxd4 (17... c6 18. h3 $14) 18. Nxd4 $16 Qd7 19. Rd1 (
19. Qe5 $5 c6 20. Re1 $16) 19... Re8 $11 {Black threatens to win material:
Re8xe1} 20. Qd2 Nb6 21. h3 {Controls g4} (21. Qf4 $142 $14) 21... h5 $4 {
letting the wind out of his own sails} (21... c5 $5 {should be considered} 22.
Nxf5 Qxf5 $11) 22. Qg5 $4 {with this move White loses his initiative} (22. Qh6
$142 {and White can look forward to a comfortable game} c6 23. Nf3 $18) 22...
c5 $14 23. Nxf5 Qxf5 24. Qxf5 gxf5 25. Kf1 Kg7 26. Bc2 {White threatens to win
material: Bc2xf5} Kf6 27. Rd6+ Re6 {Black threatens to win material: Re6xd6}
28. Rd2 f4 29. b3 {Consolidates a4+c4} Ke7 (29... h4 30. Rd8 $14) 30. c4 (30.
Bd1 Rd6 31. Rxd6 Kxd6 32. Bxh5 Nd5 $16) 30... Na8 $2 (30... Nd7 $142 $5 $14 {
would allow Black to play on}) 31. Rd5 $18 Rd6 (31... b6 32. Rxh5 Nc7 33. Rf5
$18) 32. Be4 (32. Rxc5 {makes it even easier for White} Rd2 33. Be4 Rxa2 34.
Bxb7 Nb6 35. Rxh5 Nd7 $18) 32... Ra6 (32... Rxd5 33. Bxd5 (33. cxd5 $6 Nc7 $14)
33... Nc7 34. Bxb7 $18) 33. a4 (33. Rxc5 $5 {seems even better} Rxa2 34. Bxb7
Nb6 35. Rxh5 Nd7 $18) 33... Rb6 34. Bc2 Rc6 (34... Nc7 35. Rxc5 Ne6 36. Rxh5
$18) 35. Rxh5 Nc7 36. Be4 Rb6 37. Rxc5 Ne6 (37... Kd6 38. Ra5 Rxb3 39. Rxa7 Rb4
40. Bxb7 Rxc4 $18) 38. Rb5 Rxb5 39. cxb5 Nd4 (39... Nc5 40. Bd5 $18) 40. Bd5 (
40. Bxb7 $142 $5 {might be the shorter path} Nxb3 41. Bd5 Nd4 $18) 40... b6 41.
g4 fxg3 42. fxg3 f6 43. Kf2 Kf8 (43... f5 {cannot change destiny} 44. Ke3 Nc2+
45. Kd2 $18) 44. g4 Kg7 45. Kg3 Ne2+ 46. Kh4 (46. Kf3 {makes it even easier
for White} Ng1+ 47. Kg2 Ne2 $18) 46... Nf4 (46... Kh6 47. Bc4 Nd4 48. Kg3 $18)
47. Bc4 Kh6 48. Bf7 (48. Kg3 $142 $5 {keeps an even firmer grip} Ng6 $18) 48...
Kg7 49. Bc4 Kh6 50. Kg3 Ng6 51. h4 Ne5 (51... Kg7 {is no salvation} 52. Bd3 Ne5
53. Bc2 $18) 52. Kf4 Ng6+ 53. Kg3 {Twofold repetition} Ne5 54. Be6 Ng6 55. Bf5
Ne7 56. Be4 Kg7 57. Kf4 Kh6 (57... Nc8 {is not much help} 58. Ke3 $18) 58. g5+
fxg5+ (58... Kg7 {doesn't get the bull off the ice} 59. g6 $18) 59. hxg5+ Kg7 (
59... Kh5 {hardly improves anything} 60. Bc6 Ng6+ 61. Kf5 Ne7+ 62. Kf6 Ng8+ 63.
Kf7 Kxg5 64. Kxg8 $18) 60. Ke5 Kf8 61. Ke6 Ke8 62. g6 Nxg6 63. Bxg6+ Kd8 64.
Kd6 Kc8 65. Be4 (65. b4 Kb8 66. a5 bxa5 67. bxa5 Kc8 68. Be4 Kd8 69. a6 Ke8 70.
