{C68: Ruy Lopez: Exchange Variation, sidelines} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6
4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. O-O Bg4 6. h3 Bxf3 7. Qxf3 Nf6 8. d3 Be7 9. Nc3 O-O 10. Be3 Re8
$146 (10... c5 11. Kh1 Nd7 12. Qg3 Bd6 13. Qg4 Re8 14. Bg5 f6 15. Bd2 Nf8 16.
Nd5 Ne6 17. Rad1 c6 18. Ne3 Qd7 19. Nf5 Rad8 20. Be3 Bf8 21. g3 g6 22. f4 Kh8
23. Nh4 exf4 24. gxf4 Ng7 25. f5 {Elgabry,M (2271)-Abdel Aziem,R (2230) Cairo
2000 1/2-1/2 (60)}) 11. Rad1 c5 12. Rfe1 c6 {Controls b5+d5} 13. Ne2 Qc7 14.
Ng3 g6 {Prevents intrusion on f5+h5} 15. Bg5 {White threatens to win material:
Bg5xf6} Kg7 16. c3 h6 17. Bxf6+ Bxf6 18. Ne2 (18. Qg4 Kh7 $11) 18... Rad8 19.
Qg3 Qe7 20. Qf3 Rd7 21. Qe3 Red8 22. Qd2 $2 (22. f4 $142 $15 {and White can
hope to survive}) 22... c4 $1 $19 {Deflection: d3} 23. d4 (23. dxc4 Rxd2 {
Deflection Pinning}) 23... exd4 24. Nxd4 $4 {terrible, but what else could
White do to save the game?.} (24. cxd4 Qxe4 25. Qb4 b5 $19) 24... Bxd4 (24...
c5 $142 {and Black wins} 25. e5 Bxe5 $19 (25... cxd4 $6 {is no comparison} 26.
exf6+ Qxf6 27. Rb1 $19)) 25. cxd4 $17 Rxd4 26. Qxd4+ Rxd4 27. Rxd4 b5 (27...
Qe5 $142 28. Rxc4 Qxb2 $17) 28. f3 $4 (28. e5 $142 $15 {this is the best way
to fight back}) 28... Qb4 29. Rb1 Qa4 (29... Qc5 {seems even better} 30. Rbd1
b4 31. Kh1 $19) 30. a3 Qc2 31. Rdd1 a5 32. Rdc1 Qd3 33. Rd1 (33. Kf2 h5 $19)
33... Qe3+ 34. Kf1 h5 (34... Qb3 $142 $5 $19) 35. Rbc1 $17 a4 36. Rc3 Qc5 37.
Ke2 h4 38. Rd2 $4 {sad, but how else could White save the game?} (38. Kf1 Kf6
$17) 38... Qg5 (38... Qg1 $142 $19 {it becomes clear that Black will call all
the shots}) 39. Kd1 Qc5 40. Ke2 Qg1 41. Rd7 (41. Rdc2 $19 {is still a small
chance}) 41... Qxg2+ 42. Ke3 Qxb2 43. Kd4 Qd2+ 44. Kc5 Qxc3 45. Rd4 Qe3 46. e5
(46. f4 {does not help much} c3 47. Kxc6 Qxd4 48. e5 c2 49. Kc7 c1=Q+ 50. Kb7
Qd7+ 51. Kb6 Qcc6+ 52. Ka5 Qd2#) 46... Qxe5+ 47. Kb4 (47. Rd5 {does not win a
prize} Qxd5+ 48. Kb6 Qd4+ 49. Kc7 c3 50. f4 c2 51. Kb7 c1=Q 52. f5 Qd7+ 53. Ka6
Qc5 54. f6+ Kxf6 55. Ka5 Qda7#) 47... Qxd4 48. f4 (48. Ka5 {doesn't change
anything anymore} c3 49. Ka6 c2 50. f4 c1=Q 51. f5 Qf1 52. fxg6 Qxh3 53. gxf7
Qc8+ 54. Ka5 Qa8#) 48... c3+ 49. Ka5 c2 (49... Qa7+ 50. Kb4 c2 51. f5 gxf5 52.
Kc3 c1=Q+ 53. Kb4 Qc4#) 50. Ka6 c1=Q 51. Kb7 (51. f5 {does not solve anything}
Qce3 52. f6+ Kxf6 53. Kb7 Qd8 54. Kxc6 Qeb6#) 51... Qdxf4 (51... Qcc5 52. f5
Qd7+ 53. Kb8 Qf8#) 52. Ka6 (52. Ka7 {cannot undo what has already been done}
Qc7+ 53. Ka6 b4 54. axb4 Qc4+ 55. b5 Qxb5#) 52... Qb8 53. Ka5 Qc3+ (53... Qc3+
54. Ka6 Qxa3 55. Ka5 Qa7#) (53... Qc5 54. Ka6 Qbb6#) 0-1

